gomodel:SYNGO_1166  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In this study, Belizaire et al. performed subcellular fraction of mouse brain to investigate the localization of synaptogyrin 3. Immunoblot analysis of equivalent amounts of protein showed an enrichment of synaptogyrin 3 in the synaptic vesicle fraction (LP2, Fig. 2, lane 5). As a positive control, fractionation samples were also blotted for the synaptic vesicle proteins synaptogyrin 1 and synaptophysin. Both of these proteins were also enriched in the LP2 fraction. Also, the authors performed immunocytochemistry on cultured hippocampal neurons and investigate the co-localization of synaptogyrin 3 with SV2 protein as synaptic vesicle marker. A high degree of colocalization was observed between the two proteins (Fig. 4). Moreover, in the peripheral nervous system synaptogyrin 3 was enriched in neuromuscular junctions (Fig. 5)\n\n5/2/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Mouse brain fractionation was performed as previously described (Huttner et al., 1983; Janz et al., 1998)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-05" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1166" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

